tooltips.serviceId: The unique identifier of the service in hexadecimal format (e.g., 0x1234). This ID must be unique within the system.
tooltips.instanceId: The instance identifier of the service in hexadecimal format (e.g., 0x5678). Multiple instances of the same service can exist with different instance IDs.
tooltips.unicastAddress: The unicast IP address that hosts the service instance. Required for external services when service discovery is disabled.
tooltips.reliableTcp: Enable reliable TCP communication for this service. TCP provides guaranteed delivery and error checking.
tooltips.tcpPort: The TCP port number for reliable communication. Must be between 1 and 65535.
tooltips.enableMagicCookies: Enable magic cookies for TCP connections. Magic cookies help detect if the remote endpoint supports SOME/IP protocol.
tooltips.unreliableUdp: Enable unreliable UDP communication for this service. UDP provides faster communication but without delivery guarantees.
tooltips.udpPort: The UDP port number for unreliable communication. Must be between 1 and 65535.

validation.atLeastOneProtocol: At least one communication protocol must be enabled

tooltips.enableServiceDiscovery: Specifies whether the Service Discovery is enabled
tooltips.initialState: Specifies the initial Service Discovery state after startup
tooltips.multicastAddress: The multicast address which the messages of the Service Discovery will be sent to (default: 224.224.224.0)
tooltips.port: The port of the Service Discovery (default: 30490)
tooltips.protocol: The protocol that is used for sending the Service Discovery messages
tooltips.initialDelayMin: Minimum delay before first offer message (default: 0)
tooltips.initialDelayMax: Maximum delay before first offer message (default: 3000)
tooltips.repetitionsBaseDelay: Base delay sending offer messages within the repetition phase (default: 10)
tooltips.repetitionsMax: Maximum number of repetitions for provided services within the repetition phase (default: 3)
tooltips.cyclicOfferDelay: Cycle of the OfferService messages in the main phase (default: 1000)
tooltips.requestResponseDelay: Minimum delay of a unicast message to a multicast message for provided services and eventgroups (default: 2000)
tooltips.offerDebounceTime: Time which the stack collects new service offers before they enter the repetition phase (default: 500)
tooltips.findDebounceTime: Time which the stack collects non local service requests before sending find messages (default: 500)
tooltips.findInitialDebounceReps: Number of initial debounces using find_initial_debounce_time (default: 0, valid values: 0-255)
tooltips.findInitialDebounceTime: Time which the stack collects new service requests before they enter the repetition phase during initial startup (default: 200)
tooltips.ttl: Lifetime of entries for provided services as well as consumed services and eventgroups (default: 0xFFFFFF)
tooltips.maxRemoteSubscribers: Maximum possible number of different remote subscribers. Additional remote subscribers will not be acknowledged (default: 3)
tooltips.waitRouteNetlinkNotification: Enables the tracking of the route state on_net_interface_or_route_state_changed (default: true)
